# .clinerules

## Network Troubleshooting Mode

When the user reports network errors or connectivity issues:

### Error Classification
- ECONNREFUSED → Service not running, wrong port, firewall rejecting
- ECONNRESET → Firewall reset, server crash, keepalive timeout
- ETIMEDOUT → Network unreachable, firewall drop, DNS timeout
- ENOTFOUND → DNS resolution failure
- Proxy errors → Proxy not running or misconfigured
- SSL/TLS errors → Certificate chain, expiry, CA trust
- HTTP 5xx → Server-side issue

### Diagnostic Sequence
1. `ping <host>` → basic connectivity
2. `nslookup <host>` → DNS resolution
3. `nc -zv <host> <port>` or `Test-NetConnection` → port check
4. `curl -vvv https://<host>` → full HTTP/SSL debug
5. Check proxy env vars and tool-specific proxy configs

### Resolution Patterns
- No internet → Check cable/WiFi, restart router
- DNS fails → Switch to 8.8.8.8, flush cache
- Proxy down → Start Clash/V2Ray, verify port 7890
- npm fails → `npm config set registry https://registry.npmmirror.com`
- pip fails → `pip config set global.index-url https://pypi.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/simple`
- git fails → `git config --global http.proxy http://127.0.0.1:7890`
- SSL error → Update CA bundle, check cert dates
- docker fails → Configure daemon.json with mirror
